item.strainsofascension.guidebook_artifa: Ch.41 - Strain Meter
Abyss Delvers Guidebook

§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 41:§r§r
Strain Meter

  The strain meter is an essential and common artifacts used by elite delvers. It appears as a normal golden clock with  different degrees of polishing. The shinier,

the stronger. Mechanically they work just like normal clocks. However once you hold one in your hands, you will start to feel the energy of the abyss. Using this artifacts delvers will move in ways as to delay the effects of the abyss to a deeper point without even knowing they do. This

results in the delvers seemingly getting effected by the strains at lower depths then their comrades. It also appears this effect will happen if the meter is not even held in hand. Meaning you can have in your backpack and still have the positive effects of the it.
Therefore, this tool is an essential for elite delvers. §k1234§r
Ch.34 - Nether lead
Abyss Delvers Guidebook

§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 34:§r§r
Nether Lead

  The Nether lead is a common artifacts that despite its relatively small rarity finds almost no use by delvers. It channels the energy of the abyss allowing for the

use of Layer 9 Portals outside of the zone described in chapter 19. It has only ever been used once by the whites. While common, there does not appear to be different qualities of the Nether Lead. More information on the subject can be found in Chapter 19 and 15. §k1234§r
Ch.44 - Spell of Collection
Abyss Delvers Guidebook

§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 44:§r§r
Spell of Collection

  The spell of Collection is a valuable artifacts used by delvers who hunt for resources and those of the whites when going on long lasting

It is often described as an arcane book. The writing within unintelligible. Nothing is known about the content. However its use is well documented. The book appears to channel the energy of the abyss into the tools of the delver. In its working it is identical to the effect of the

mending enchantment. However only the legendary Master Spell of Collection appears to be capable of channeling this energy through the delvers arm into his tool. The other spell of collection books only channel the energy to the armor worn by the delvers. §k1234§r
Ch.35 - Poison Talisman
Abyss Delvers Guidebook

§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 35:§r§r
Poison Talisman

  The poison talisman is an artifacts that is used only by elite delvers and the whites. It appears to reduce the chance of being mutated and consequently

poisoned in the lower layers of the abyss. There are different qualities but not much is known about the exact workings of the artifacts as few have ever ventures this deep. The most potent of these carry a label stating their their creator 'Trulim'.
There is no confirmed information on him or his creations. §k1234§r
Ch.36 - Gravity Talisman
Abyss Delvers Guidebook

§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 36:§r§r
Gravity Talisman

  The Gravity talisman is a common artifact that uses the energy of the abyss to make the delver wearing it feel lighter. This results in an increased jumping
power that, while only small, has saved many in dire situations before. There do not appear to be different qualities of the Gravity Talisman. §k1234§r
Ch.38 - Shield of the Whites
Abyss Delvers Guidebook

§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 38:§r§r
Shield of the Whites

  The shield of the White is a legendary artifact that is among the rarest of all known. It's power so great that all known to exist are used by the whites on their

expeditions. The exact workings are rarely talked about. The only confirmed information is that it appears to channel the abyss energy into the one holding it, making him stronger in the progress. §k1234§r
Ch.39 - Prism of Sloth
Abyss Delvers Guidebook

§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 39:§r§r
Prism of Sloth

  The prism of Sloth is an powerful artifact used by elite delvers and the whites. It has the ability the decrease the energy robbing one of his sight in the lower
layers of the abyss. While it can not prevent delvers from going blind, it increases the potency of night vision potions that are commonly used to counter the blindness. §k1234§r
Ch.40 - Wither Talisman
Abyss Delvers Guidebook

§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 40:§r§r
Wither Talisman

  The wither Talisman is similar to the Poison talisman in its workings. It lowers the chance mutation of delvers in the deepest layers of the abyss.
Similarly to the poison talisman there are some that carry the label 'Trulim' which are believed to be among the most potent of wither talisman. §k1234§r
Ch.33 - Artifacts
Abyss Delvers Guidebook

§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 33:§r§r
Artifacts

  Artifacts are relics of an ancient time. Found deep in the underground that often appear to be ordinary items at first. However their power should never

be underestimated. They are an essential tool for any elite delver that wants to explore below the third layer. Most artifacts can be found in different qualities ranging from the common 0 star artifacts to legendary 5 star artifacts. However getting yourself any artifact

is not trivial as the knowledge on their creating has long been forgotten. The only way one can hope to acquire an artifacts is by finding one in the underground. Either left their in an ancient time or by fellow delvers that meet an early end in the abyss. Should you get

your hands on one, be sure to reference their power with the book. All known artifacts are listed in the chapters to follow. Additionally, be sure to protect your artifacts well. They will often be stolen by thiefs or worse by pica spirits. For more information see chapter 26. §k1234§r

item.strainsofascension.guidebook_layer1:
§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 7:§r§r
Layer 1

 First off, the point at which you will feel the strains taking effect, is not consistent. There are days, where you can go about 20 meters and not feel a strain.

Other days, you will already feel them at 10 meters. Researchers have hypothesized, it might be related to the moon phases.
The first strains you will encounter, are not too far below. After around 10-20 meters under sea level, your arms will start to feel heavy, making

exploration and mining very difficult. Even though, the first layer doesn't appear too threatening, you should still take care. The layers to come are not for the faint of heart, especially after layer 3. §k1234§r
item.strainsofascension.guidebook_layer2:
§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 8:§r§r
Layer 2

 If you go beyond the first layer, you will find yourself struggling to fight back in addition to the exhaustion from the first layer. Delvers must take care and
bring adequate gear before venturing to this depth. Even trivial monsters can become severe threats should your equipment break in this depth. §k1234§r
item.strainsofascension.guidebook_layer3:
§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 9:§r§r
Layer 3

  The effects of the third layer are intense hunger in addition to the effects of the first two layers. However, as long as enough rations are brought

the dangers are somewhat mitigated. Though you should never venture this deep without sufficient food reserves. This is the last layer normal delvers are allowed to enter for safety reasons. No help will be sent to those who choose to ignore the rule and venture even further. §k1234§r
item.strainsofascension.guidebook_layer4:
§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 10:§r§r
Layer 4


§4§lWARNING §r

§4VENTURING TO THIS LAYER IS FORBIDDEN FOR NORMAL DELVERS!§r§0

§4No help will be sent!§r§0
In addition to the effects of the third layer, the effect of the 4th layer is extreme weakness in the knees. This results in a huge reduction in speed making combat difficult. §k1234§r
item.strainsofascension.guidebook_layer5:
§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 11:§r§r
Layer 5


§4§lWARNING §r

§4VENTURING TO THIS LAYER IS FORBIDDEN FOR NORMAL DELVERS!§r§0

§4No help will be sent!§r§0

In addition to the effects of the 4rd layer, the 5th layer result in blindness. While the blindness is only temporary it is extremely difficult to fight in it. Great care must be taken. Elite Delvers use special night vision potions to counteract the effect temporarily. While expensive they can

save your life should you ever need to fight in this depth.
Good luck! §k1234§r
item.strainsofascension.guidebook_layer6:
§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 12:§r§r
Layer 6


§4§lWARNING §r

§4VENTURING TO THIS LAYER IS FORBIDDEN FOR NORMAL DELVERS!§r§0

§4No help will be sent!§r§0

The effects of the 6th layer appear to be the largely the same as those of the fifth. The reason it is still classified as a layer is that the effects seem to be stronger then before. However, the whites have reported that this layer is thinner then most others. Specifics are unknown

as few have ever ventured this deep.
Good luck! §k1234§r
item.strainsofascension.guidebook_layer7:
§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 13:§r§r
Layer 7


§4§lWARNING §r

§4VENTURING TO THIS LAYER IS FORBIDDEN FOR NORMAL DELVERS!§r§0

§4No help will be sent!§r§0

The strains of the 7th layer include all of the 6th. Additionally ones body seems to be mutating. This results in extreme nausea and severe reactions. Death is likely. The whites use special medicine to counteract this.
Good luck! §k1234§r
item.strainsofascension.guidebook_layer8:
§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 14:§r§r
Layer 8


§4§lWARNING §r

§4VENTURING TO THIS LAYER IS FORBIDDEN FOR NORMAL DELVERS!§r§0

§4No help will be sent!§r§0

The strains of the 8th layer include all of the the strains of the 7th layer. One you enter this layer, death is almost guaranteed. Only few ever left this layer without withering away at its effects. Not much is known on the specifics as there are only few who survived entering this

layer. All of those who did were either to severely injured to talk about it of seem to have forgotten all about it.
Good luck! §k1234§r
item.strainsofascension.guidebook_layer9:
§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 15:§r§r
Layer 9

  The effects of the 9th layer are unknown. While the aforementioned expedition did reveal its existence, nothing else is known about the effects. The

letter that was pulled up from the expedition team was mostly unintelligible expect for a few words. "exists" "red" "blood" were among the words that could be read on the note. 

The boundary between the 8th and 9th layer is made up by thick black bedrock. Normal

tools can not penetrate the boundary making it impossible to travel there by descending. Instead, delvers must construct a portal. Details on the contruction can be found in Chapter 19. Scientists believe that these portals use the energy of the abyss to transport the

delvers to the 9th layer.
Good luck! §k1234§r
item.strainsofascension.guidebook_layers:
§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 6:§r§r
Layers of the Abyss

  It is said, that once, the abyss was a local phenomena. However for unknown reasons, the effects of the abyss have now spread everywhere. Though, the under-

ground is riddled with countless sources of dangers, one specific danger is worse than all of them. We call it 'strains'. One who enters the underground is certain to encounter the strains of the abyss.

The abyss can be divided into 9 known layers, all of which have a specific strain. Not only are the strains in the deeper layers more severe, but also cumulative. Meaning one who is affected by the strains of the 3rd layer will also receive the strains of

the first and second layer. This makes it extremely dangerous to go to the lower layers, as returning will put an immense stress on the delver's body and mind. In the following chapters, the layers and their strains will be described in further detail.

§nDelvers are advised to not go beyond the third layer for their own safety.§r

Only elite delvers are allowed to venture in to the depth below the third layer and only a handful have ever set foot in the 7th layer. Though, the 8th layer has been successfully entered,

it would be certain death for the average human. There is one documented journey attempting to go beyond the 8th layer and into the 9th. While none of the delvers in the expedition survived the journey, the existence of the 9th layer has been confirmed by a letter
which was pulled up using a rope. §k1234§r
item.strainsofascension.guidebook_portal:
§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 19:§r§r
The Nether Portal

  Accessing the 9th layer of the abyss, also known as the nether is impossible by normal means. Instead delvers have to use what is known as a portal to get

there. Currently scientists believe that portals use the energy of the abyss to teleport delvers to the nether. This theory is based on the fact that the portal will only teleport delvers when used in the 7th layer and below. While it can be constructed above the 7th layer, it will

not teleport delvers as there seems to be to little energy to do so. Additionally there is at least one known artifact that seems to channel the abyss energy, thus making it possible to use the portal at any height.

More information on that subject can be found found in the
item.strainsofascension.guidebook_spawne:
§k1234567890abcdefghijklmnopqrstuv§r

§n§lChapter 26:§r§r
Spawner

  One of the many dangers of the abyss are dungeons. Especially the spawners within them. Aside from the fact that they spawn enemies, which while

they do not pose much of a thread alone, can become quite troublesome when appearing in numbers or in unexpected situations. These monsters aside, there is a bigger threat to delvers. Within the spawners live Pica spirits. These spirits are known for stealing items and

However, they very rarely attack delvers without being provoked. Once a spawner is destroyed, the spirit within vanishes. Though, there is a way to fight the spirit. Pica spirits are easily upset by the sound of bells. This has been discovered by the whites. When disturbed

by bell sounds, the spirit will teleport out, away from the spawner and destroying it in the progress. It is possible to follow the spirit. If done correctly, the spirit will not be able to flee again and can be fought by the delvers. Great care must be taken though, as
fighting the spirit can become a serious health concern. §k1234§r
